The paper is about Presentation Attack Detection (PAD) in facial recognition systems, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a new evaluation framework and dataset, which involves machine learning (cs.MM), and proposes a benchmark for evaluating the performance of PAD methods, which involves both machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
